## Functions

### copy&#95;if&#95;else() {#abd1fd06683a32de0138c4ba80b0836b4}

<MemberDefinition
  template={<>template &lt;class InputIt, class OutputIt1, class OutputIt2, class UnaryPredicate&gt;</>}
  prototype={<>static std::pair&lt; OutputIt1, OutputIt2 &gt; copy&#95;if&#95;else (InputIt First, InputIt Last, OutputIt1 d1, OutputIt2 d2, UnaryPredicate Predicate)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
Copy elements in the range &#91;First, Last) to d1 when the predicate is true or d2 when the predicate is false.

This is essentially both std::copy&#95;if and std::remove&#95;copy&#95;if combined into a single pass.

Definition at line <a href="#l00072">72</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/mips/lib/target/mips/mctargetdesc/mipselfobjectwriter-cpp">MipsELFObjectWriter.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

### find&#95;best() {#a268abe30400a55226d690105cc187f01}

<MemberDefinition
  template={<>template &lt;class InputIt, class UnaryPredicate, class Comparator&gt;</>}
  prototype={<>static InputIt find&#95;best (InputIt First, InputIt Last, UnaryPredicate Predicate, Comparator BetterThan)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
Find the best match in the range &#91;First, Last).

An element matches when <a href="/docs/api/classes/predicate">Predicate(X)</a> returns FindBest&#95;Match or FindBest&#95;PerfectMatch. A value of FindBest&#95;PerfectMatch also terminates the search. BetterThan(A, B) is a comparator that returns true when A is a better match than B. The return value is the position of the best match.

This is similar to std::find&#95;if but finds the best of multiple possible matches.

Definition at line <a href="#l00098">98</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/mips/lib/target/mips/mctargetdesc/mipselfobjectwriter-cpp">MipsELFObjectWriter.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

### getMatchingLoType() {#af29f17b9965a9f3bdcbbfafbf90b7f0c}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>static unsigned getMatchingLoType (<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/elfrelocationentry">ELFRelocationEntry</a> &amp; Reloc)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
Determine the low relocation that matches the given relocation.

If the relocation does not need a low relocation then the return value is ELF::R&#95;MIPS&#95;NONE.

The relocations that need a matching low part are R&#95;(MIPS|MICROMIPS|MIPS16)&#95;HI16 for all symbols and R&#95;(MIPS|MICROMIPS|MIPS16)&#95;GOT16 for local symbols only.

Definition at line <a href="#l00122">122</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/mips/lib/target/mips/mctargetdesc/mipselfobjectwriter-cpp">MipsELFObjectWriter.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

<Link id="l00332" /><CodeLine lineNumber="332"><span class="doxyHighlight">&#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00333" /><CodeLine lineNumber="333"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00334" /><CodeLine lineNumber="334"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Sort relocation table entries by offset except where another order is</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00335" /><CodeLine lineNumber="335"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// required by the MIPS ABI.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00336" /><CodeLine lineNumber="336"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00337" /><CodeLine lineNumber="337"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// MIPS has a few relocations that have an AHL component in the expression used</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00338" /><CodeLine lineNumber="338"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// to evaluate them. This AHL component is an addend with the same number of</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00339" /><CodeLine lineNumber="339"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// bits as a symbol value but not all of our ABI&#39;s are able to supply a</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00340" /><CodeLine lineNumber="340"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// sufficiently sized addend in a single relocation.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00341" /><CodeLine lineNumber="341"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00342" /><CodeLine lineNumber="342"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// The O32 ABI for example, uses REL relocations which store the addend in the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00343" /><CodeLine lineNumber="343"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// section data. All the relocations with AHL components affect 16-bit fields</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00344" /><CodeLine lineNumber="344"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// so the addend for a single relocation is limited to 16-bit. This ABI</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00345" /><CodeLine lineNumber="345"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// resolves the limitation by linking relocations (e.g. R&#95;MIPS&#95;HI16 and</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00346" /><CodeLine lineNumber="346"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// R&#95;MIPS&#95;LO16) and distributing the addend between the linked relocations. The</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00347" /><CodeLine lineNumber="347"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// ABI mandates that such relocations must be next to each other in a</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00348" /><CodeLine lineNumber="348"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// particular order (e.g. R&#95;MIPS&#95;HI16 must be immediately followed by a</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00349" /><CodeLine lineNumber="349"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// matching R&#95;MIPS&#95;LO16) but the rule is less strict in practice.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00350" /><CodeLine lineNumber="350"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00351" /><CodeLine lineNumber="351"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// The de facto standard is lenient in the following ways:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00352" /><CodeLine lineNumber="352"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// - &#39;Immediately following&#39; does not refer to the next relocation entry but</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00353" /><CodeLine lineNumber="353"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   the next matching relocation.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00354" /><CodeLine lineNumber="354"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// - There may be multiple high parts relocations for one low part relocation.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00355" /><CodeLine lineNumber="355"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// - There may be multiple low part relocations for one high part relocation.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00356" /><CodeLine lineNumber="356"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// - The AHL addend in each part does not have to be exactly equal as long as</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00357" /><CodeLine lineNumber="357"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   the difference does not affect the carry bit from bit 15 into 16 This is</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00358" /><CodeLine lineNumber="358"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   to allow, for example, the use of %lo(foo) and %lo(foo+4) when loading</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00359" /><CodeLine lineNumber="359"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   both halves of a long long.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00360" /><CodeLine lineNumber="360"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00361" /><CodeLine lineNumber="361"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// See getMatchingLoType() for a description of which high part relocations</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00362" /><CodeLine lineNumber="362"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// match which low part relocations. One particular thing to note is that</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00363" /><CodeLine lineNumber="363"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// R&#95;MIPS&#95;GOT16 and similar only have AHL addends if they refer to local</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00364" /><CodeLine lineNumber="364"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// symbols.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00365" /><CodeLine lineNumber="365"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00366" /><CodeLine lineNumber="366"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// It should also be noted that this function is not affected by whether</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00367" /><CodeLine lineNumber="367"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// the symbol was kept or rewritten into a section-relative equivalent. We</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00368" /><CodeLine lineNumber="368"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// always match using the expressions from the source.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00369" /><CodeLine lineNumber="369" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/anonymous-namespace-mipselfobjectwriter-cpp-/mipselfobjectwriter/#a5fb8605e7260a242de5a25e2b3add57d"><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">void</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/anonymous-namespace-mipselfobjectwriter-cpp-/mipselfobjectwriter/#a5fb8605e7260a242de5a25e2b3add57d">MipsELFObjectWriter::sortRelocs</a>(</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mcassembler">MCAssembler</a> &amp;Asm,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00370" /><CodeLine lineNumber="370"><span class="doxyHighlight">                                     std::vector&lt;ELFRelocationEntry&gt; &amp;Relocs) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00371" /><CodeLine lineNumber="371"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// We do not need to sort the relocation table for RELA relocations which</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00372" /><CodeLine lineNumber="372"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// N32/N64 uses as the relocation addend contains the value we require,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00373" /><CodeLine lineNumber="373"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// rather than it being split across a pair of relocations.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00374" /><CodeLine lineNumber="374"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mcelfobjecttargetwriter/#a18895a2343e1b4a90083d13c8ddc90cd">hasRelocationAddend</a>())</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00375" /><CodeLine lineNumber="375"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">return</span><span class="doxyHighlight">;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00376" /><CodeLine lineNumber="376"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00377" /><CodeLine lineNumber="377"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Sort relocations by the address they are applied to.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00378" /><CodeLine lineNumber="378"><span class="doxyHighlight">  <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a74cdbd1e4f731e7d7cd83461b8b1de0b">llvm::sort</a>(Relocs,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00379" /><CodeLine lineNumber="379"><span class="doxyHighlight">             &#91;&#93;(</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/elfrelocationentry">ELFRelocationEntry</a> &amp;<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/ir/builtingcs-cpp/#a2e38c85003a042421cde1647632d0b72">A</a>, </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/elfrelocationentry">ELFRelocationEntry</a> &amp;<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/ir/builtingcs-cpp/#ae76959fe811ba090de4cba69ac00f1da">B</a>) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00380" /><CodeLine lineNumber="380"><span class="doxyHighlight">               </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">return</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/ir/builtingcs-cpp/#a2e38c85003a042421cde1647632d0b72">A</a>.Offset &lt; <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/ir/builtingcs-cpp/#ae76959fe811ba090de4cba69ac00f1da">B</a>.Offset;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00381" /><CodeLine lineNumber="381"><span class="doxyHighlight">             &#125;);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00382" /><CodeLine lineNumber="382"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00383" /><CodeLine lineNumber="383"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Place relocations in a list for reorder convenience. Hi16 contains the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00384" /><CodeLine lineNumber="384"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// iterators of high-part relocations.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00385" /><CodeLine lineNumber="385"><span class="doxyHighlight">  std::list&lt;MipsRelocationEntry&gt; Sorted;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00386" /><CodeLine lineNumber="386"><span class="doxyHighlight">  <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvector">SmallVector&lt;std::list&lt;MipsRelocationEntry&gt;::iterator</a>, 0&gt; Hi16;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00387" /><CodeLine lineNumber="387"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">for</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">auto</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> &amp;R : Relocs) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00388" /><CodeLine lineNumber="388"><span class="doxyHighlight">    Sorted.push&#95;back(R);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00389" /><CodeLine lineNumber="389"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (<a href="#af29f17b9965a9f3bdcbbfafbf90b7f0c">getMatchingLoType</a>(R) != ELF::R&#95;MIPS&#95;NONE)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00390" /><CodeLine lineNumber="390"><span class="doxyHighlight">      Hi16.<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvectortemplatebase/#af42bfbc067df27c19ee2fc859df58799">push&#95;back</a>(std::prev(Sorted.end()));</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00391" /><CodeLine lineNumber="391"><span class="doxyHighlight">  &#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00392" /><CodeLine lineNumber="392"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00393" /><CodeLine lineNumber="393"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">for</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">auto</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/support/md5-cpp/#ac0eafdc9ee161b71e7af98af736952fd">I</a> : Hi16) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00394" /><CodeLine lineNumber="394"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">auto</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> &amp;R = <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/support/md5-cpp/#ac0eafdc9ee161b71e7af98af736952fd">I</a>-&gt;R;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00395" /><CodeLine lineNumber="395"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">unsigned</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> MatchingType = <a href="#af29f17b9965a9f3bdcbbfafbf90b7f0c">getMatchingLoType</a>(R);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00396" /><CodeLine lineNumber="396"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// If the next relocation is a perfect match, continue;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00397" /><CodeLine lineNumber="397"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (std::next(<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/support/md5-cpp/#ac0eafdc9ee161b71e7af98af736952fd">I</a>) != Sorted.end() &amp;&amp;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00398" /><CodeLine lineNumber="398"><span class="doxyHighlight">        <a href="#a0b9745f3db31eb4f80f4acdaff1bbe76">isMatchingReloc</a>(MatchingType, R, std::next(<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/support/md5-cpp/#ac0eafdc9ee161b71e7af98af736952fd">I</a>)-&gt;R))</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00399" /><CodeLine lineNumber="399"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">continue</span><span class="doxyHighlight">;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00400" /><CodeLine lineNumber="400"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Otherwise, find the best matching low-part relocation with the following</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00401" /><CodeLine lineNumber="401"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// criteria. It must have the same symbol and its addend is no lower than</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00402" /><CodeLine lineNumber="402"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// that of the current high-part.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00403" /><CodeLine lineNumber="403"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00404" /><CodeLine lineNumber="404"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// (1) %lo with a smaller offset is preferred.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00405" /><CodeLine lineNumber="405"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// (2) %lo with the same offset that is unmatched is preferred.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00406" /><CodeLine lineNumber="406"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// (3) later %lo is preferred.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00407" /><CodeLine lineNumber="407"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">auto</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> Best = Sorted.end();</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00408" /><CodeLine lineNumber="408"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">for</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">auto</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> J = Sorted.begin(); J != Sorted.end(); ++J) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00409" /><CodeLine lineNumber="409"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">auto</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> &amp;R1 = J-&gt;R;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00410" /><CodeLine lineNumber="410"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (R1.Type == MatchingType &amp;&amp; R.Symbol == R1.Symbol &amp;&amp;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00411" /><CodeLine lineNumber="411"><span class="doxyHighlight">          R.Addend &lt;= R1.Addend &amp;&amp;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00412" /><CodeLine lineNumber="412"><span class="doxyHighlight">          (Best == Sorted.end() || R1.Addend &lt; Best-&gt;R.Addend ||</span></CodeLine>
